urlText: L1 Dulwich Hill Line weekend trackwork
content:
From Saturday 31 October to Sunday 1 November, buses replace light rail services daily from 6am to 11pm between The Star and Dulwich Hill in both directions on the L1 Dulwich Hill Line to allow for WestConnex constructions and other maintenance works.

During this period, replacement buses will be running at the following frequency:
  • 6am to 7am – 8 to 15 minutes
  • 7am to 7pm – 6 to 10 minutes
  • 7pm to 11pm – 8 to 15 minutes
Please follow the directional signs to the nearby replacement bus stop locations.

The light rail replacement bus services are Opal enabled. You will need to tap on when boarding a replacement bus and tap-off when arriving at your stop. Opal readers are located in all replacement buses.

A standard light rail fare applies on-board light rail replacement buses.

Contactless payment methods are not accepted on replacement bus services.

Normal services will resume from 6am Monday 2 November.
subtitle: L1 Dulwich Hill Line weekend trackwork

urlText: Trackwork between Fairfield and Glenfield, then continue to Macarthur
content:
Saturday 14 and Sunday 15 November
  • Buses replace trains between Fairfield and Glenfield, then continue to Macarthur.
  • Trains run to the normal timetable between Fairfield and the City.
  • Trains also run between Leppington and the City via the T8 Airport & South Line.
  • On Saturday from 7.45am until 11.45am, the all-stations Homebush trains run between Ashfield and the City only.
  • Leppington trains make extra stops at Homebush and Croydon. T1 Western Line Penrith trains make an extra stop at Burwood. 
  • On Saturday from 10pm until 4am, buses also replace trains between Leppington and Glenfield, then continue to East Hills.
  • On Sunday from 6.30am until 10.30am, buses replace the all-stations Homebush trains between Ashfield and Central.
  • Leppington trains make extra stops at Homebush and Croydon.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
